title: For Sale:  Star BKM 9mm with 2 mags and original box
postcontent: This is not the same pistol as the surplus Star BM's are steel framed, this is a Star BKM, this differs by having an aluminum frame which cuts the weight from 34.5oz (Star BM) to 25.9oz (Star BKM). Similar operation to a 1911, minus the grip safety,though lighter and thinner.Without the Star BKM there would have not been the Sig P938, there was a gunsmith that used to convert these into a smaller version called the Lafrance Nova 6-pack which is the basis of the Sig P938 design with some small differences. The Star pistols when the safety is engaged moves the hammer out of alignment with the sear and blocks the slide from any movement, on the P938 it does the same but the slide can still be moved.The Star BKM comes in the original box with included cleaning kit, manual and 2 8 round magazines, for the price of $375,transfer to be done at Tigard Pawn 4 More or A Cut Above Pawn.

title: For Sale:  Savage 10 FCP-SR .308
postcontent: This is a hard to find Savage 10 FCP-SR in digital camo (the Savage Manufacturer part number is 19480).  It's chambered in .308/7.62 NATO.  This isn't the new model FCP-SR that's on every shelf in every box store.  Guys who shoot long range know this is a vastly superior build compared to the new model.  I configured this rifle for a long range class I took in Virginia that was taught by Dan Newbury. The rifle features a 24 inch heavy fluted barrel with a muzzle break, a one piece picitinny rail, digital camo AccuStock, AccuTrigger, and an all steel construction 10 round detachable box magazine by Accurate Mag Company.  In addition to that, I have a 6-18 Vortex Crossfire II scope with a level attached, a cheek riser, and an imitation Harris bipod.  I zeroed the rifle at a hundred yards last August, cleaned it, oiled it, and put it away.  The only adjustment I never made to it is on the magazine feed lip.  I never bothered to buy the adjustment tool because I feed the ammo by hand one round at a time when I shoot long range.  The mag feed lip probably needs to be opened up about 3 thousandths or so to get the cartridges to feed more smoothly.  The adjustment tool costs about 25 bucks.If you have any questions, feel free to ask.  If the ad is up, the rifle is still for sale.  1000 dollars gets everything I listed in the ad.  900 gets you everything but the optic.  Not looking for trades at this time.
